== Other versions of the legendarium ==
In the earlier versions of the [[Quenta Silmarillion]], Olwë was named ''Elwë'' (while his brother Thingol also had the name ''Sindo''<ref>{{LR|Lhammas}}, ''Of the tongues of the Elves in Middle-earth, and of the Noldorin that returned thither'', p. 174</ref>), and there it was Olwë who was one of the [[Three Ambassadors]] instead of his brother Thingol.<ref>{{LR|Quenta}}, ''Commentary on Chapter 3(a)'', p. 217</ref> Neither did the existence of his daughter Eärwen or her marriage to Finarfin emerge yet.

